{"key":"post-9645245","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9645245</id>\n<content>They crack in the cool down phase if the PC cools off too fast.&amp;nbsp; AA pressure cookers aren't quite as bad about it as others, because their thickness allows for a slightly slower cool down.&amp;nbsp;  At the end of the cycle, try reducing your stove to its lowest setting, rather than off.&amp;nbsp; After half an hour or so, shut it off.&amp;nbsp; Remember, the pressure inside your jars is also 15 psi, so if the PC itself loses pressure faster than the jars do, they'll break.&amp;nbsp; Mason jars are designed to hold vacuum, but not pressure.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9653366</next>\n<prev>9645223</prev>\n<first>9644146</first>\n<last>9655240</last>\n<when>1232476685</when>\n<utime>01/20/09 08:38 PM</utime>\n</post>"}